    "Immanuel Kant's three critiques are:",
    "Critique of Pure Reason (1781): This critique deals with metaphysics and epistemology, exploring the nature of knowledge and reality.",
    "Kant argues that human understanding is limited to the realm of experience and that we can never know things as they are in themselves, independent of our perceptions. 2.",
    "Critique of Practical Reason (1788): In this critique, Kant examines ethics and morality, arguing that moral laws are based on reason rather than emotion or desire.",
    "He introduces the concept of the \"categorical imperative,\" which is a moral principle that should be willed as a universal law. 3."
  ],
